r 2018 as the licenses were renegotiated. And it\u2019s not on", "id": 1097405, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/explained/448860/music-video-game-tv-licensing-rights-problems", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 258, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Do TV shows and movies lose rights to songs like video games do?", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-06T17:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/concord_ship.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-none\"><em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/24211550/concord-ps5-pc-beta-player-numbers\">Concord</a></em> is a competent, well-made game. Or rather it <em>was</em>. I\u2019m going to struggle with tense when it comes to writing about <em>Concord</em>, because, as of Sept. 6, <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/gaming/447033/concord-ps5-pc-pulled-refunds-sony-firewalk\">the game has been shut down indefinitely</a>, just two weeks into its existence. Will it ever come back? Firewalk Studios, which developed the game for Sony, says it\u2019s taking <em>Concord</em> offline and refunding buyers while it \u201cdetermine[s] the best path ahead.\u201d But it\u2019s difficult to envision a healthier", "id": 1096969, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gaming/448883/a-good-game-like-concord-just-isnt-good-enough-anymore", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 258, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "A good game like Concord just isn\u2019t good enough anymore", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-06T16:36:44+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"A stylized image from System Shock 2 shows a woman\u2019s face made of gray metal covered with circuit-board effects, surrounded by green lightning\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2013/04/SS.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em>Ed. note: A version of this personal essay from the author of </em>Soon I Will Be Invincible<em> and the new superhero novel </em>Fight Me<em> originally ran in 2013. </em></p>\n\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-none\">When I finished college, I applied for jobs in publishing. I wanted to be a literary young man and be part of a recycled idea of a passionate, groundbreaking creative intelligentsia. I don&#8217;t know that I would have admitted it to myself, but it&#8217;s true.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">But I didn&#8217;t ", "id": 1096970, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/2013/4/18/4231940/how-to-write-video-games", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 258, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Working on video games taught me how to write", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-06T16:10:09+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24836622/baldurs_gate_3_romance_astarion.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em>Baldur\u2019s Gate 3</em> continues to reign as <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/23648669/best-video-games-2023#vhCpZe\">one of greatest RPGs</a> of all time. Even at full price we called it <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/23974928/bg3-baldurs-gate-3-best-deal-black-friday-2023\">gaming\u2019s best deal</a> \u2014\u00a0something you can easily spend hundreds of hours playing and still have more to see after multiple playthroughs. The game has further evolved since its release with a number of free, content-rich updates, including <a href=\"https://baldursgate3.game/news/patch-7-now-live_121\">this week\u2019s Patch 7</a> that added new evil", "id": 1096555, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/good-deals/448744/baldurs-gate-3-sale-pc-steam-larian-studios", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 258, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Get Baldur\u2019s Gate 3 for its lowest price yet this weekend", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-06T15:41:40+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Sony\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25550589/24hkvhjq.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/24201430/ps5-astro-bot-lego-horizon-adventures-hands-on\"><em>Astro Bot</em></a>, the second full-fledged title featuring the de facto PlayStation mascot and a <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/review/447564/astro-bot-review\">very good Nintendo-tier platformer</a>, has arrived. To commemorate the occasion, <a href=\"https://blog.playstation.com/2024/07/29/first-look-astro-bot-limited-edition-dualsense-wireless-controller/\">PlayStation has launched</a> a limited edition DualSense controller fashioned after the blue-eyed bot. The $79.99 controller is technically available now, but you might have a dif", "id": 1096556, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/24208796/playstation-astro-bot-controller-dualsense-where-to-buy", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 258, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Where can I find that adorable Astro Bot controller?", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-06T14:08:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/ankerusbchero.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The only thing better than a durable, braided USB-C cable is one that can charge two gadgets at the same time. That\u2019s exactly what <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B0CRZ6JJ6D\">Anker\u2019s 2-in-1 USB-C cable</a> does, and it\u2019s $4 off its normal $25.99 price if you\u2019re an Amazon Prime member. With it, you can charge a duo of gadgets ranging in power requirements, from your phone and Steam Deck to your wireless earbuds, controller, tablet, laptop, and whatever else you own that gets a charge from that near-ubiquitous port. As for me, this will be great for charging the electric snot sucker that we use with our infant. (This is a real thing \u2014\u00a0parents will know.)</p>\n", "id": 1096019, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/good-deals/448388/usbc-cable-two-in-one-charging-anker-amazon-deal", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 258, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Anker&#8217;s two-headed USB-C cable is a $22 blessing", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-06T14:02:47+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/08/NBXmas-set-on-transparent.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Lego fans of every age, wouldn&#8217;t you like to see something strange? It\u2019s not-quite-but-almost-soon-to-be <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OBeVDXx1bIQ\">Halloween</a>, which is the start of a marathon of holidays that <em>The Nightmare Before Christmas</em> can claim under its purview. Tim Burton and Henry Selick\u2019s stop-motion animated musical is a <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/23914691/best-horror-movies-for-kids-spoopy-h